@0 = ~Hello! No time to chat, I have to tend to the sick and wounded.~/*你好！ 你不必这么讽刺无礼。*/
@1 = ~It looks like an infirmary. Can you fix me up?~/*你看起来像个冒险者。 你可以训练我吗？*/
@2 = ~Why are there so many sick people here? I hope it's not the plague.~/*为什么有这么多人在这里？ 告诉我关于瘟疫的事情。*/
@3 = ~好，我要走了。~
@4 = ~Sorry, <SIRMAAM>.My knowledge is not sufficient for this. Speak to Neurik at the temple, he will surely help you.~/*抱歉，<SIRMAAM>。我的错，我不会再打扰你了。 如果你杀了孩子，我只好杀了你。*/
@5 = ~The plague? No, of course not. These are common sick people, as well as warriors who have been wounded. If you'll excuse me, I'll mind my own business.~/*瘟疫 “不，当然不。” 别害怕，只要你放我出来就会得到你的奖赏了。 我觉得你最好管你自己的事就好……*/
@6 = ~Sorry, no time to talk, I have to tend to the sick and wounded.~/*对不起，德金。你得自己去找你的冒险。*/
@7 = ~You know, I'm an aspiring writer. I've just finished working on a novel based on true events in the life of the great but misunderstood Drizzt Do'Urden. If you have a few minutes, I can read you a passage.~
/*不，我要留着它。 它在潘尼苏拉区东边的一所房子的地下室里。如果你发现任何就回来，我付给你酬金。*/